message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper is about a new crowdsourced dataset for reading comprehension that focuses on coreference resolution. This falls under the subfield of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) in arXiv. The paper also discusses the performance of state-of-the-art reading comprehension models, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), hence cs.AI is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves evaluating models based on their ability to reason and understand language, which falls under the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
